==歷史沿革==
===起源===
大約公元前2500年在Ibagwa附近所發現的陶器和之後在恩蘇卡發現的伊博人作品有相同之處，起源於在阿南布拉山谷Umueri氏族的傳統。1970年代時，奧韋裡, 奧基奎, 奧爾呂, 奧古, 烏迪 和奧卡部落決定從語言和文化的證據組成「一個伊博中心地帶」。<ref>{{cite book|title=A History of the Igbo People|last=Elizabeth|first=Isichei|publisher=London: Macmillan|year=1976|isbn=0-333-18556-0}}; excerpted in "[http://books.google.com/books?id=oHt6gmjbpewC&pg=PA75 Cultural Harmony I: Igboland — the World of Man and the World of Spirits] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=oHt6gmjbpewC&pg=PA75 |date=20131207122948 }}", section 4 of Kalu Ogbaa, ed., ''Understanding Things Fall Apart'' (Westport, Conn.: Greenwood Press, 1999; ISBN 0-313-30294-4), pp. 83–85.</ref>

===尼日王國===
[[File:Bronze_head_and_ram's_head.jpg|thumb]]
尼日人在伊博人居住的土地上創造了一個神話，這個神話是存在於伊博人分布的各地區諸多創世神話中的一個。尼日人和阿古萊里人都屬於Umueri氏族，能夠回溯他們的譜系到宗法王Eri。<ref name=isichei246/>雖然Eri被Chukwu上帝描述為一個“sky being”，但他的起源尚不清楚。<ref name=isichei246/><ref name=Uzukwu>{{cite book |last=Uzukwu |first=E. Elochukwu |title=Worship as Body Language |year=1997 |isbn=0-8146-6151-3 |page=93 |publisher=Liturgical Press |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9hhmzVrYPHAC&pg=PA93 |access-date=2016-03-24 |archive-date=2014-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107192011/http://books.google.com/books?id=9hhmzVrYPHAC&pg=PA93 |dead-url=no }}</ref>他的特徵為最早擁有社會階級的阿南布拉人。歷史學家Elizabeth Allo Isichei說：「尼日人和阿古萊里人都屬於Umueri氏族，是一個都能共同追溯到Eri的伊博群體。」<ref>{{cite book |title=A History of African Societies to 1870 |page=246 |isbn=0-521-45599-5 |first=Elizabeth Allo |last=Isichei |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=LqIVnr9h7DsC&pg=PA246 |accessdate=2008-12-13 |year=1997 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |archive-date=2014-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107191951/http://books.google.com/books?id=LqIVnr9h7DsC&pg=PA246 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

考古證據顯示，在Igboland的尼日霸權可能可以追溯到公元9世紀<ref>{{cite book |last=Hrbek |first= Ivan; Fāsī, Muḥammad |title=Africa from the Seventh to the Eleventh Century |url=https://archive.org/details/generalhistoryaf00fasi |publisher=Unesco  |location=London |year=1988 |page=[https://archive.org/details/generalhistoryaf00fasi/page/n279 254] |isbn=92-3-101709-8 }}</ref>，而已出土的皇家墓葬可以追溯到至少10世紀。Eri是如神般的尼日創始人，被認為大約在13世紀後遷居到伊博文化相關的地區。<ref name=lovejoy62>{{cite book | last = Lovejoy | first = Paul | title = Identity in the Shadow of Slavery | publisher = Continuum International Publishing Group | page=62| year = 2000 | isbn  = 0-8264-4725-2|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=yEHVCsSFRUcC&pg=PA62}}</ref>他直接緊隨在第一個尼日之王Ìfikuánim後。根據[[伊博語|伊博語]]的口語傳統，他的統治始於1043，<ref>{{cite book |title= Igbo Civilization: Nri Kingdom & Hegemony |first=M. Angulu |last=Onwuejeogwu |publisher=Ethnographica |year=1981 |isbn=0-905788-08-7 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=hWm4AAAAIAAJ}}</ref>但至少有一個以上的歷史學家提出Ìfikuánim的統治時期要晚得許多，他們認為大約在公元1225年。<ref>{{cite book |title=Murder at Montpelier: Igbo Africans in Virginia |first=Douglas B. |last=Chambers |edition=illustrated |publisher=Univ. Press of Mississippi |year=2005 |isbn=1-57806-706-5 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=PrPxWLSrp78C&pg=RA1-PA33 |page=33}}</ref>

每個國王都追溯他們的始祖Eric，每個國王都遵從Eric的宗教禮儀。新國王的成年禮（成為Ezenri（尼日的祭司王））過程非常嚴格，遵循由英雄所建立尼日王國的路徑。<ref>{{cite book|last=Uzukwu |first=E. Elochukwu |title=Worship as Body Language |year=1997 |isbn=0-8146-6151-3 |page=93 |publisher=Liturgical Press |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9hhmzVrYPHAC&pg=PA98}}</ref>

尼日王國是一個宗教政體，一個[[政教合一|政教合一]]的國家，在伊博地區的中心腹地發展。<ref name=lovejoy62/> 尼日人有七種禁忌，其中包括人（如雙胞胎出生）、動物（如殺或吃蟒蛇）、<ref>{{cite book |title=The Archaeology of Contextual Meanings |first=Ian |last=Hodder |edition=illustrated |publisher=CUP Archive |year=1987 |isbn=0-521-32924-8 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Pv48AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA72 |page=72 |access-date=2016-03-24 |archive-date=2014-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107191958/http://books.google.com/books?id=Pv48AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA72 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 對象、時間、行為、言語和地點的禁忌。<ref name=Nritaboo>{{cite book | last = Nyang | first = Sulayman; Olupona, Jacob K. | title = Religious Plurality in Africa: Essays in Honour of John S. Mbiti | publisher = Mouton de Gruyter | location = Berlin | year = 1995 | isbn = 3-11-014789-0 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=Fg3wuR95hk8C&pg=PA118 | page = 118 | access-date = 2016-03-24 | archive-date = 2014-01-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140107191956/http://books.google.com/books?id=Fg3wuR95hk8C&pg=PA118 | dead-url = no }}</ref>這些禁忌用於教育和管理海外印度人。這意味著，雖然某些伊博人可能有不同的生活形式，但是所有伊博宗教的信徒都必須遵守信仰的原則，並服從在地球上的代表the Eze Nri.。<ref name=Nritaboo/><ref>{{cite book |title=The Archaeology of Contextual Meanings |first=Ian |last=Hodder |edition=illustrated |publisher=CUP Archive |year=1987 |isbn=0-521-32924-8 |page=72}}</ref>

