16到19世紀晚期，發生在跨大西洋的奴隸貿易，年輕人被送走，加上戰爭也增加了對俘虜的使用，對伊博人產生了巨大的影響。大多數伊博奴隸在比夫拉灣（也稱為伯尼的海岸線）運出。<ref>{{cite book |title=Territorial Disputes and Resource Management: A Global Handbook |first=Rongxing |last=Guo |publisher=Nova Publishers |year=2006 |isbn=1-60021-445-2 |page=130 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=z5Le627xQLgC&pg=PA130 |access-date=2016-03-24 |archive-date=2017-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411221742/https://books.google.com/books?id=z5Le627xQLgC&pg=PA130 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 這個區域包括現代的[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]東南部，西[[喀麥隆|喀麥隆]]，赤道[[幾內亞|幾內亞]]地區和北部的部分地區。<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/64296/Bight-of-Biafra |title=Bight of Biafra |publisher=Britannica Online Encyclopedia |accessdate=2008-11-19 |archive-date=2008-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081226192108/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/64296/Bight-of-Biafra |dead-url=no }}</ref>在該地區的商品和奴隸貿易的主要港口包括[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的邦尼和卡拉巴爾鎮。大量來自比夫拉灣的奴隸本來是伊博人。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.informaworld.com/smpp/content~db=all~content=a714005225~tab=content |last=Chambers |first=D.B. |publisher=Routledge, part of the Taylor & Francis Group |title=REJOINDER – The Significance of Igbo in the Bight of Biafra Slave |accessdate=2009-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite encyclopedia |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/73213/Bonny |title=Bonny |publisher=Britannica Online Encyclopedia |accessdate=2008-12-27 |archive-date=2008-12-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081229145312/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/73213/Bonny |dead-url=no }}</ref>奴隸通常是由阿羅邦聯綁架或從伊博村莊買奴隸賣給歐洲人。<ref>{{cite book |title=Murder at Montpelier: Igbo Africans in Virginia |first=Chambers B. |last=Douglas |publisher=Univ. Press of Mississippi |year=2005 |isbn=1-57806-706-5 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=PrPxWLSrp78C&pg=PA25 |page=25 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2017-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421011924/https://books.google.com/books?id=PrPxWLSrp78C&pg=PA25 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 多數的伊博奴隸都是掃蕩奴隸戰爭或出征的受害者，而且有時發生可憎之事或罪行時，他們總被認為是罪魁之首。<ref>{{cite book|title=The physical anthropology of Southern Nigeria |last1=Talbot |first1=Percy Amaury |first2=H. |last2=Mulhall |page=5 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1962}}</ref>在英國殖民者的眼中，伊博奴隸是叛逆的，且為了逃脫奴隸身分，[[自殺|自殺]]率極高。<ref>{{cite book|title=Trans-Atlantic Dimensions of Ethnicity in the African Diaspora |last=Lovejoy |first=Paul E. |isbn=0-8264-4907-7 |publisher=Continuum International Publishing Group |year=2003 |pages= 92–93}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Voices of the Poor in Africa |first=Elizabeth Allo |last=Isichei |publisher=Boydell & Brewer |year=2002 |page=81}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The River Flows on: Black Resistance, Culture, and Identity Formation in Early America |first=Walter C. |last=Rucker |isbn=0-8071-3109-1 |publisher=LSU Press |year=2006 |page=52}}</ref>不知是甚麼原因，有證據顯示，交易商尋求伊博婦女。<ref>{{cite book |title=Africanisms in American Culture |first=Joseph E. |last=Holloway |publisher=Indiana University Press |year=2005 |page=32 |isbn=0-253-21749-0 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TmzTyI5rfDMC&pg=PA32 |location=bottom of 3rd paragraph |accessdate=2008-12-19 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626181714/http://books.google.com/books?id=TmzTyI5rfDMC&pg=PA32 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Writing African History |first=John Edward |last=Philips |page=412 |publisher=Boydell & Brewer |year=2005 |isbn=1-58046-164-6 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=1UeW6zHYT30C&pg=PA412 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2017-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421011544/https://books.google.com/books?id=1UeW6zHYT30C&pg=PA412 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

與一般大眾的認知相反，歐洲的奴隸販子相當了解各種非洲種族，導致某些族裔群體容易成為種植園主的首選。他們特別喜歡的民族因而相當集中在美洲的某些地區。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.historynow.org/03_2005/historian3.html |publisher=History Now |title=African Immigration to Colonial America |first=Ira |last=Berlin |quote=(paragraph 11) Preferences on both side of the Atlantic determined, to a considerable degree, which enslaved Africans went where and when, populating the mainland with unique combinations of African peoples and creating distinctive regional variations in the Americas. |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080919230942/http://www.historynow.org/03_2005/historian3.html |archive-date=2008-09-19 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>伊博奴隸被送至殖民地，如[[牙買加|牙買加]]、[[古巴|古巴]]、[[圣多明各|圣多明各]]、[[巴巴多斯|巴巴多斯]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Black Experience and the Empire |first=Philip D. |last=Morgan |author2=Sean Hawkins |isbn=0-19-926029-X |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2004 <!--|nopp=416--> |page=82 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=kG824iVy1BsC&pg=PA82 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2016-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416211005/https://books.google.com/books?id=kG824iVy1BsC&pg=PA82 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[美國|美國]]<ref name=yorku>{{cite web |url=http://www.yorku.ca/nhp/areas/ethnic.htm |quote="''As is now widely known, enslaved Africans were often concentrated in specific places in the diaspora...USA (Igbo)''" |publisher=York university |title=Ethnic Identity in the Diaspora and the Nigerian Hinterland |location=Toronto, Canada |accessdate=2008-11-23 |archive-date=2008-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081022185349/http://www.yorku.ca/nhp/areas/ethnic.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[伯利茲|伯利茲]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Africana |year=1999 |url=https://archive.org/details/africanaencyclop00appi |first=Anthony |last=Appiah |author2=Henry Louis Gates |isbn=0-465-00071-1 <!--|nopp=2095--> |page=[https://archive.org/details/africanaencyclop00appi/page/212 212]}}</ref>和[[特立尼達和多巴哥|特立尼達和多巴哥]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Roots and Branches |first=Michael |last=Craton |isbn=0-08-025367-9 |publisher=University of Waterloo Dept. of History<!--|nopp=292-->|page=125}}</ref>等.

伊博文化的元素仍然可以在這些地方找到。例如，在[[牙買加|牙買加]]土語裡，伊博字中"unu"(您)，意思是“你”的複數，仍在使用。<ref>{{cite book |title=Defining Creole |first=John H. |last=McWhorter |publisher=Oxford University Press US |year=2005 |isbn=0-19-516670-1 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=zdxJJVY54nYC&pg=PA217 |page=217 |accessdate=2009-01-10}}</ref> “Red Igbo”（或“red eboe”）該術語源自伊博人膚色突變的發病率，但受到東邊[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的影響，嚴格說起來可能不是伊博語。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080113/focus/focus4.html |last=Robotham |first=Don |title=Jamaica and Africa (Part II) |publisher=Gleaner Company |date=January 13, 2008 |quote=...It is not possible to declare that the Eastern Nigerian influence in Jamaica – apparent in expressions such as 'red ibo' – is Igbo. |accessdate=2008-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081226220329/http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080113/focus/focus4.html |archive-date=2008-12-26 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> ''BIM''是[[巴巴多斯|巴巴多斯]]是一個口語術語，在[[巴巴多斯|巴巴多斯]]普遍被奴役使用，這個詞是從"BEM"衍生的，在伊博語意為“我的地方或是我的人」，但可能有其他來源。<ref>{{cite book |title=Dictionary of Caribbean English Usage |first=Richard |last=Allsopp |author2=Jeannette Allsopp |page=101 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=PmvSk13sIc0C&pg=PA101 |publisher=University of the West Indies Press |year=2003 |others=Contributor Richard Allsopp |isbn=976-640-145-4 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2016-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506091516/https://books.google.com/books?id=PmvSk13sIc0C&pg=PA101 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Carrington, Sean |title=A~Z of Barbados Heritage |year=2007 |publisher=Macmillan Caribbean Publishers Limited|page=25 |isbn=0-333-92068-6}}</ref> 原本的伯利茲城在伊博人移民之後改叫伊博城。<ref>{{cite book|title=British Honduras: an historical and descriptive account of the colony from its settlement, 1670 |url=https://archive.org/details/britishhondurash00gibbuoft |first=Archibald Robertson |last=Gibbs |publisher=S. Low, Marston, Searle & Rivington |year=1883 |quote="Eboe Town, a section of the town of Belize reserved for that African tribe, was destroyed by fire"}}</ref>在美國，伊博奴隸最常到切薩皮克灣殖民地和[[馬里蘭州|馬里蘭州]]和[[弗吉尼亞|弗吉尼亞]]，在那裡他們構成了非洲人的最大群體。<ref>{{cite book |title=Bound Away: Virginia and the Westward Movement |first1=David Hackett |last1=Fischer |first2=James C. |last2=Kelly |publisher=University of Virginia Press |year=2000 |isbn=0-8139-1774-3 |page=62 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=GFa7KVPWmKwC&pg=PA62 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704171054/http://books.google.com/books?id=GFa7KVPWmKwC&pg=PA62 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Hog and Hominy: Soul Food from Africa to America |first=Frederick Douglass |last=Opie |publisher=Columbia University Press |year=2008 |isbn=0-231-14638-8 |page=18 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9lAl8f11qngC&pg=PA18 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704165455/http://books.google.com/books?id=9lAl8f11qngC&pg=PA18 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 自20世紀後期，強大的就業市場吸引了[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的移民在[[馬里蘭州|馬里蘭州]]定居，他們主要是使用[[英語|英語]]和[[伊博語|伊博語]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.usefoundation.org/userdata/file/Research/languages_of_the_usa.pdf |format=PDF |title=list of languages #25 along with Kru and Yoruba |publisher=U.S. ENGLISH Foundation, Inc. |accessdate=2009-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220090800/http://www.usefoundation.org/userdata/file/Research/languages_of_the_usa.pdf |archive-date=2009-02-20 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

===殖民地時期===
在[[英國|英國]]殖民統治的努力下，19世紀[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的伊博人和[[尼日爾河|尼日爾河]]的其他民族接觸，導致了不同的伊博人深化了他們的民族認同。在伊博人共同的決定下，他們懷抱[[基督教|基督教]]和西方教育。<ref>{{cite book |title=Missionary Enterprise and Rivalry in Igboland, 1857–1914
|first=Felix K. |last=Ekechi |edition=illustrated |publisher =by Routledge |year=1972 |location=last paragraph on page 146 |page=146 |isbn=0-7146-2778-X |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=WNwgU_0wQukC&pg=PA146}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Igbo Women and Economic Transformation in Southeastern Nigeria, 1900–1960: 1900–1960 |first=Gloria |last=Chuku |edition=illustrated |publisher=Routledge |year=2005 |isbn=0-415-97210-8 |page=145 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Z3jouPZxPC4C&pg=PA145 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626213631/http://books.google.com/books?id=Z3jouPZxPC4C&pg=PA145 |dead-url=no }}</ref>由於伊博政府的分化，其中包括[[英國|英國]]需要保證酋長任命的集中式及不兼容的間接統治，[[英國|英國]]殖民統治被認為上演公開衝突因此大為緊張。在[[英國|英國]]殖民統治下，[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的主要種族和[[伊博語|伊博語]]等多樣性緩慢下降，如[[豪薩人|豪薩語]]和[[約魯巴人|約魯巴語]]。<ref>{{cite book |year=1992 |title=Groundwork of Igbo history |last=Afigbo |first=A. E. |publisher=Vista Books |location=Lagos |isbn=978-134-400-8 | pages = 522–541}}</ref>

在奇努阿·阿切貝的小說「齊諾瓦阿切」描寫到，殖民統治已形塑伊博人的社會。英國統治所帶來的文化，如引入權證酋長為統治者。<ref>{{cite book|title=Power, Marginality and African Oral Literature |first=Graham |last=Furniss |author2=Elizabeth Gunner |author3=Liz Gunner  |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1995 |isbn=0-521-48061-2 |page=67 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=G8ZDWbwIwdQC&pg=PA67}}</ref> 基督教[[傳教士|傳教士]]有時會刻意避開伊博文化的源頭，強勢地引進歐洲意識形態進入伊博人的社會和文化。<ref>{{cite book |title=Christianity and Ibo Culture |first=Edmund |last=Ilogu |publisher=Brill Archive |year=1974 |isbn=90-04-04021-8 |page=63 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0uMUAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA63 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626213628/http://books.google.com/books?id=0uMUAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA63 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 伊博婦女被徵稅的傳聞引發了1929年的伊博婦女在阿壩的戰爭（也稱為1929年阿壩騷亂），在伊博人的歷史裡，這是唯一一次婦女的大規模反抗。<ref>{{cite book |title=Female Power and Male Dominance: On the Origins of Sexual Inequality |first=Peggy Reeves |last=Sanday |edition=illustrated, reprint |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1981 |isbn=0-521-28075-3 |page=136 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=39ScGl-T3J0C&pg=PA136 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704170430/http://books.google.com/books?id=39ScGl-T3J0C&pg=PA136 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

伊博文化的其他方面也因殖民主義改變，如房屋，教育和宗教。建築的傳統是泥牆和[[茅草|茅草]]屋頂變成如房屋和[[鋅|鋅]]屋頂的水泥塊。興建車輛所行駛的道路。許多地方也興建醫院和學校。隨著這些設施的建設，電力和[[自來水|自來水]]分別裝在20世紀初。有了電，收音機和電視機也逐漸普遍，並已成為大多數伊博人家庭司空見慣的新技術。<ref name=modern>{{cite book |title=Nigeria's Diverse Peoples |first=April A. |last=Gordon |page=87 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |year=2003 |isbn=1-57607-682-2 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=H26pO3vwmHoC&pg=PA87 |accessdate=2008-12-19 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704165248/http://books.google.com/books?id=H26pO3vwmHoC&pg=PA87 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===奈及利亞比夫拉戰爭===
{{Main|尼日利亚内战}}
[[File:Flag_of_Biafra.svg|thumb]]（1967–1970）共和國的旗幟，有時被視為'''伊博族'''的民族旗幟。]]

1966年开始，居于北方的[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]与伊博人及东北地区的其它民族发生的一系列冲突，于1966年7月29日发动政府废黜由前军方領袖所组建的政府，并于1967年剌杀了[[约翰逊·阿吉伊-伊龙西|约翰逊·阿吉伊-伊龙西]]。同年内战各方在加纳的[[阿克拉|阿克拉]]举行六方和平谈判，但和谈失败<ref>
{{cite book |title=The Labour Governments 1964–1970: International Policy |first=Steven |last=Fielding |author2=John W. Young |publisher=Manchester University Press |year=2003 |page=197 |isbn=0-7190-4365-4 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=21fItelgxnwC&pg=PA197}}
</ref>
。由于和谈失败导致东尼日利亚地区宣布独立，于1967年5月30日成产新的[[比亚法拉共和国|比亚法拉共和国]]<ref name=biafradate>{{cite book |title=Nigeria: Current Issues and Historical Background |first=Martin P. |last=Mathews |publisher=Nova Publishers |page=38 |year=2002 |isbn=1-59033-316-0 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=hTs6GpM4zDMC&pg=PA38 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626195519/http://books.google.com/books?id=hTs6GpM4zDMC&pg=PA38 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 
，[[楚库埃梅卡·奥杜梅格伍·奥朱古|楚库埃梅卡·奥杜梅格伍·奥朱古]]成为其国家元首<ref>{{cite book |title=African Aims & Attitudes: Selected Documents |first=Martin |last=Minogue |author2=Judith Molloy |publisher=CUP Archive |year=1974 |page=393 |isbn=0-521-20426-7 |location=General C. O. Ojukwu |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=eBk7AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA393 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626195459/http://books.google.com/books?id=eBk7AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA393 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。由此尼日利亚陷入内战之中，战争从1967年7月6日持续至1970年1月15日 <ref name=biafradate/><ref>{{cite book |title=Memoirs of a Mbororo: The Life of Ndudi Umaru, Fulani Nomad of Cameroon |first=Henri |last=Bocquené |author2=Oumarou Ndoudi |author3=Gordeen Gorder |publisher=Berghahn Books |page=285 |year=2002 |isbn=1-57181-844-8 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9gY6_WbmfK0C&pg=PA285 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626195449/http://books.google.com/books?id=9gY6_WbmfK0C&pg=PA285 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
比亚法拉政权宣布投降为止，东部地区的伊博人遭到屠杀，如1966年反伊博运动中有约1~3万伊博人被屠杀<ref name=Diamond-1967>{{cite journal|last1=Diamond|first1=Stanley|title=The Biafra Secession|journal=Africa Today|date=June 1967|volume=14|issue=3|pages=1–2|doi=10.2307/4184781|jstor=4184781|publisher=Indiana University Press|doi_brokendate=2015-01-09}}</ref><ref name=Keil-1970>{{cite journal|last1=Keil|first1=Charles|title=The Price of Nigerian Victory|journal=Africa Today|date=January 1970|volume=17|issue=1|jstor=4185054|publisher=Indiana University Press}}</ref>。

由于英国政府在尼日利亚屠杀中不光彩的行为，招至部分人士的反对，其中包括[[让-保罗·萨特|让-保罗·萨特]]及[[约翰·列侬|约翰·列侬]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rockhall.com/inductees/john-lennon |title=John Lennon |publisher=Rock and Roll Hall of Fame + Museum |year=2007 |quote=September 1, 1969: John Lennon returns his MBE. He says it is to protest the British government's involvement in Biafra, its support of the U.S. in Vietnam and the poor chart performance of his latest single, 'Cold Turkey'. |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-date=2010-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323135641/http://rockhall.com/inductees/john-lennon/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2007年7月，[[比夫拉|比夫拉]]前領導人發聲，繼續主張[[比夫拉|比夫拉]]獨立，“唯一的選擇就是我們應該獨立......我們並不像其他人一樣屬於[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]”。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/6276820.stm |title=Call for Biafra to leave Nigeria |publisher=BBC |accessdate=2008-11-23 |date=6 July 2007 |archive-date=2009-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090107024636/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/6276820.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===近代歷史（1970年代至今）===
尼日利亞 - 比夫拉戰爭讓伊博人及伊博地區一蹶不振。戰鬥已經徹底摧毀了許多醫院，學校和家庭。除了損失了自己的積蓄，很多伊博人面臨著來自其他族裔群體和新非伊博聯邦政府的歧視。<ref name=discrim>{{cite book |title=Human Rights in Commonwealth Africa |first=Rhoda E. |last=Howard-Hassmann |page=95 |isbn=0-8476-7433-9 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |year=1986 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=B8wmGpg9nf0C&pg=PA95&dq=igbo+discrimination+nigeria |accessdate=2008-12-18 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704165414/http://books.google.com/books?id=B8wmGpg9nf0C&pg=PA95&dq=igbo+discrimination+nigeria |dead-url=no }}</ref>有些伊博人的次團體，如Ikwerre，從戰後開始與伊博主流社會分離。<ref>{{cite book |title=A Tri-Generational Study of Language Choice & Shift in Port Harcourt |first=Kelechukwu U. |last=Ihemere |page=26 |publisher=Universal-Publishers |year=2007 |isbn=1-58112-958-0 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=uwk5IkralBAC&pg=PA26 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704171536/http://books.google.com/books?id=uwk5IkralBAC&pg=PA26 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 在戰後時代，[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]東部的人改變了像[[伊博語|伊博語]]的姓名和地方的名字。例如，Igbuzo鎮被英國化，改稱''Ibusa''。<ref>{{cite book |title=Auxiliaries in Igbo Syntax: A Comparative Study |first=Nọlue |last=Emenanjọ |publisher=Indiana University Linguistics Club |year=1985 |page=64 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=CuQtAAAAMAAJ&q=Igbuzo+ibusa&dq=Igbuzo+ibusa |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704163825/http://books.google.com/books?id=CuQtAAAAMAAJ&q=Igbuzo+ibusa&dq=Igbuzo+ibusa |dead-url=no }}</ref>由於歧視，許多伊博人很難找到工作，並在1970年代初期成為[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]最貧困的少數民族之一。<ref name=discrim/><ref>{{cite book |title=Nigeria in the Twenty-first Century: Strategies for Political Stability and Peaceful Coexistence |first=Emmanuel Ike |last=Udogu |page=51 |isbn=1-59221-320-0 |publisher=Africa World Press |year=2005 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=UHE2lQn3u90C&pg=PA51&dq=igbo+discrimination |accessdate=2008-12-18 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704165815/http://books.google.com/books?id=UHE2lQn3u90C&pg=PA51&dq=igbo+discrimination |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Troubled Journey: Nigeria Since the Civil War |first=Levi Akalazu |last=Nwachuku |publisher=Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing |year=2004 |page=59 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=3MvR4mE54QUC&pg=PA59&dq=igbo+discrimination+nigeria |isbn=0-7618-2712-9 |accessdate=2008-12-18 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704170615/http://books.google.com/books?id=3MvR4mE54QUC&pg=PA59&dq=igbo+discrimination+nigeria |dead-url=no }}</ref>

Igboland公民和[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]政府的情況因之後二十年間的重建和因[[石油|石油]]工業在[[尼日爾河三角洲|尼日爾河三角洲]]地區崛起而有所好轉。這使[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]南部建立了許多新工廠，許多伊博人最終還成為政府的公家人員。<ref>{{cite book|year=1992 |title=Groundwork of Igbo history |publisher=Vista Books, Lagos, |isbn=978-134-400-8|pages= 161–177}}</ref>但也有許多人工作於私人部門，許多伊博人從事[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的商業和經濟活動。<ref>{{cite book |title=The Politics of Memory: Truth, Healing and Social Justice |first=Ifi |last=Amadiume |publisher=Zed Books |year=2000 |isbn=1-85649-843-3 |pages=104–106 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fe9dD5kIY0MC&pg=PA104 |access-date=2016-03-25 |archive-date=2014-07-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704164457/http://books.google.com/books?id=fe9dD5kIY0MC&pg=PA104 |dead-url=no }}</ref>21世紀初以來，許多[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]伊博人移民到[[歐洲|歐洲]]和[[美洲|美洲]]。<ref>
